### MED-04 · Teacher marks POST uses raw `req.json()` without [safeParseJSON](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/lib/validate.ts#61-79)

**File**: [teacher/marks/[assignmentId]/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/teacher/marks/%5BassignmentId%5D/route.ts#L72)

```typescript
const body = await req.json();
```

**What**: No try-catch on JSON parsing. If body is invalid JSON, this throws an unhandled error, returning a 500 with stack trace.

**Contrast**: Finance routes use [safeParseJSON()](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/lib/validate.ts#61-79) ✅.

