### MED-06 · Test DELETE doesn't verify existence before cascading

**File**: [admin/tests/[id]/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/tests/%5Bid%5D/route.ts#L60)

```typescript
await ProTest.findByIdAndDelete(id);
await TestAnswerKey.deleteOne({ testId: id });
await ProTestAttempt.deleteMany({ testId: id });
```

**What**: If the test doesn't exist, the function still deletes answer keys and attempts for that ID (no-ops), then returns success. Should check existence first and return 404.

