### MED-08 · Verify-OTP doesn't delete records after max attempts

**File**: [auth/verify-otp/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/auth/verify-otp/route.ts#L40)

```typescript
if (record.attempts >= 3) {
    return NextResponse.json({ message: 'Too many wrong attempts.' }, { status: 429 });
}
```

**What**: After 3 wrong attempts, the record stays in DB indefinitely. User must request a new OTP to reset the counter. The old record lingers.

