### MED-09 · Google OAuth user auto-created with `status: 'pending'` but can immediately login

**File**: [lib/auth.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/lib/auth.ts#L78-L86)

**What**: When a new Google user signs in, they're created with `status: 'pending'` and `isProfileComplete: false`. The middleware redirects them to `/complete-profile` or `/pending-approval`. However, the JWT is issued immediately, so they have a valid session token. If they know the API endpoint URLs, they could call student APIs directly before being approved.

**Mitigation**: Middleware blocks page access ✅. API middleware blocks wrong-role access ✅. But the session token IS valid — the `status` check only happens at the page level, not at the API level for their own role's routes.

---

### MED-10 · Missing database indexes on frequently queried fields

**Current indexes found**: Only `CoursePricing.courseId` (unique) and `User.rollNumber+classId` (compound unique).

**Missing indexes that will hurt at 500+ records**:

| Collection | Fields | Query Location |
|---|---|---|
| [Attendance](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Attendance.ts#10-24) | `{ 'records.student': 1 }` | student dashboard |
| [Attendance](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Attendance.ts#10-24) | `{ date: 1, subject: 1, section: 1 }` | teacher session lookup |
| [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) | `{ studentId: 1 }` | student fees page |
| [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) | `{ courseId: 1 }` | admin fee course listing |
| `ProTestAttempt` | `{ testId: 1 }` | admin test detail |
| [FeePayment](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeePayment.ts#13-33) | `{ student: 1 }` | cascade delete |
| `Salary` | `{ employee: 1, month: 1 }` | duplicate check |
| `DocumentSubmission` | `{ requirement: 1, student: 1 }` | upload duplicate check |

