# 🟢 LOW — Nice to Have

---

### LOW-01 · Admin bcrypt rounds inconsistent
- Register: `bcrypt.hash(password, 12)` — 12 rounds ✅
- Admin user create: `bcrypt.hash(password, 10)` — 10 rounds
- Standard: Both should use 12.

### LOW-02 · No `try-catch` on several routes
Routes missing top-level try-catch (will crash with unhandled exception):
- [admin/attendance/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/attendance/route.ts) (GET, PATCH, PUT)
- [admin/users/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/route.ts) (GET, POST, DELETE)
- [student/attendance/self-mark/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/attendance/self-mark/route.ts)
- `teacher/attendance/[id]/session/route.ts`

### LOW-03 · `EmailOTP` records never cleaned up
No TTL index or cleanup job. Old OTP records accumulate forever.

### LOW-04 · Contact form validates phone but accepts non-numeric chars
Phone regex: `^[\d\s\+\-\(\)]{7,15}$` — allows `+---(())` without any digits to be valid.

### LOW-05 · Test `startedAt` from client is trusted for timing
The M-03 fix accepts `startedAt` from the client. A sophisticated user could send a `startedAt` 1 minute ago to bypass the time limit. Should store `startedAt` server-side (in a Redis/DB record) when GET is called.

### LOW-06 · Complete-profile uploads files sequentially
Additional files in document upload are processed one-by-one in a `for` loop. Should use `Promise.all` for parallel upload.

### LOW-07 · Salary duplicate check is not atomic
```typescript
const exists = await Salary.findOne({ employee, month });
if (exists) return 409;
// ... gap here — another request could create one ...
const record = await Salary.create({ ... });
```
Between the check and the create, a duplicate could slip through under concurrent requests. Fix: Add a unique compound index on `{ employee, month }`.

